also a prolific writer of novels and youth books with intriguing titles such as 
"Sandwich," "Rainbow Jordan" and "When the Rattlesnake Sounds." A native of 
Charleston, S.C., she acted and directed with the American Negro Theatre. On 
Sunday in New York of cancer. 
