<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Girls' Rompers Recalled Due to Hazardous Ornaments: The Consumer Product 
Safety Commission said that necklaces attached to three styles of the garments 
could cause strangulation.The necklaces, about 26 inches long with a small 
stuffed doll hanging from the end, could become snagged or twisted around a 
child's neck, the commission said. Best Wear Inc. of Los Angeles is recalling 
style numbers 84P1580 and 84P1581, labeled "Baby's 2 PCS Romper-Doll," and 
84P1065, "Baby's 3 PCS Blouse-Romper-Doll." About 1,200 of them were sold in 
Los Angeles-area stores in April. The commission advised that the necklaces be 
removed and the rompers returned for refunds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
