</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three months of undercover investigation led to the arrest of a Camarillo man 
and the seizure of more than two pounds of marijuana and assorted other drugs 
and paraphernalia, authorities said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials from the East Valley Sheriff's Department narcotics unit arrested 
Steve Rivera, 25, about 9 p.m. Wednesday after purchasing half an ounce of 
cocaine and two pounds of marijuana from Rivera through undercover detectives 
over the length of the investigation, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies executed a search warrant at Rivera's home in the 200 block of 
Peoples Street in Camarillo late Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Inside the home they found 2 1/2 pounds of marijuana, an ounce of cocaine, 19 
ampuls of anabolic steroids, 21 syringes and four grams of hashish, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 No estimated street value of the illegal drugs and paraphernalia was provided 
by investigators. 
</P>
<P>
 Rivera was arrested on suspicion of possession of marijuana and cocaine, 
possession for sale of marijuana and cocaine, and possession of dangerous 
drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 He is in custody at Ventura County Jail in lieu of $20,000 bail and is 
scheduled to be arraigned today in Ventura County Municipal Court. JEFF 
McDONALD 
