</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback College's radio station is seeking musical performers for its show 
that airs the work of up-and-coming talent. 
</P>
<P>
 The radio station, KSBR-FM, is accepting tapes from solo musicians and groups 
that are not under contract to any record company, and whose music fits into 
the station's contemporary jazz format. 
</P>
<P>
 Night and weekend specialty shows on the station also feature reggae, folk, 
bluegrass, ragtime, rock, Latin jazz, blues, hip-hop and big-band music. 
</P>
<P>
 Terry Wedel, the station's program director, said new artists often have 
trouble getting their music played to a wider audience. Wedel said music for 
the station's "Unsigned Talent" segments will be played during KSBR's regular 
format or during the appropriate specialty shows. 
</P>
<P>
 Artists who are interested should send a high-quality cassette tape, biography 
and telephone number to KSBR-FM, 28000 Marguerite Parkway, Mission Viejo, CA 
92692. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 582-5727. 
