<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: AGOURA HILLS; CITY ASKS RESIDENTS TO RECYCLE MOTOR OIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MANNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Agoura Hills wants residents to dispose of their used motor oil in 
an environmentally safe manner. 
</P>
<P>
 "People are dumping it in trash, in storm drains, in landfills, and it ends up 
in streams leading to the beach," said Mike Kamino, the city's senior planner. 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura Hills residents can bring their used motor oil to Agoura Hills 10 
Minute Lube at 29338 Roadside Drive for recycling.  
</P>
<P>
 The facility is certified by the state as an authorized collection center, 
Kamino said. The service station contracts out to a hauler who takes the used 
oil to a recycling facility. 
</P>
<P>
 The establishment is open Monday through Friday from 8 a.m. to 5:30 p.m.; 
Saturday from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m.; and Sunday from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 There is a 20-gallon-per-day limit on the amount of oil that can be brought 
in, Kamino said. 
</P>
<P>
 Any oil that is suspected of being contaminated with other pollutants like 
antifreeze or brake fluid will not be accepted. FRANK MANNING 
</P>
</TEXT>
