GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; HARLEY LOVE RIDE SIGN-UPS TO BEGIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE RYFLE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Registration begins Saturday in Glendale for Love Ride 11, the annual 
motorcycle caravan, as Harley lovers raise funds for the Muscular Dystrophy 
Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 About 500 motorcyclists, plus celebrities and charity officials, are expected 
at a press conference at 11 a.m. Saturday to kick off sign-ups for the event, 
at Harley-Davidson of Glendale, 3717 San Fernando Road.More than 16,000 riders 
are expected to take part in the Love Ride on Nov. 13 from Glendale to Castaic 
Lake. "We started out 11 years ago with 600 riders and raising $42,000," said 
Gary Provenzano, an organizer of the event. "This year we hope to raise $1.5 
million." 
</P>
<P>
 Beginning Saturday, participants can pick up pledge forms, which can be turned 
in the day of the ride. 
</P>
<P>
 Information on registration can be obtained by calling (818) 246-5618. STEVE 
RYFLE 
