GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; TECHNICIAN TRAINING PROGRAM OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A new program for men and women interested in manufacturing technician jobs 
will begin Monday at Glendale Community College. 
</P>
<P>
 Courses will train students in blueprint reading, computer repair, 
computer-aided drafting, soldering and aviation structural design.  
</P>
<P>
 Financial-aid and counseling services are available. Under the Job Training 
Assistance Partnership Act (JTPA), economically disadvantaged women may also 
receive additional assistance in registration, tuition, transportation and 
child-care costs.  
</P>
<P>
 An orientation session about the program and what it takes to qualify for JTPA 
assistance will take place at 10:30 a.m. today in Room 107 of the main campus 
trailer court. For information, call (818) 240-1000, Ext. 5497. ANTONIO OLIVO 
