<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: AREA GOLFERS TAKE AIM AT U.S. MID-AMATEUR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Caballero Country Club in Tarzana will play host to a qualifier for the 
U.S. Women's Mid-Amateur championship today beginning at 7 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The field of 54 includes Jody Duclos of Moorpark and Linda Chen Olsen of 
Granada Hills, each of whom played in the U.S. Women's Amateur last week in 
Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
 Players are vying for 18 available berths over 18 holes of stroke play.The 
Mid-Amateur is Sept. 10-15 at Tacoma Golf and Country Club in Tacoma, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
 Other area entrants include Reiko Watanabe, Desiree Dontas and Sylvia Kim of 
Wood Ranch Country Club; Rosanne Minasian, Yumi Saito and Katherine Sullivan of 
the Sepulveda Women's Club; Sandra Silverstone of Braemar; Catherine Swanson of 
Olivas Park and Betty Pfahler of Crystalaire. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mid-Amateur, gaining in popularity because college-age players are 
excluded, is open to players 25 and older with an index of 9.4 or less. 
</P>
<P>
 El Caballero, one of the most difficult courses in the region, has a par of 
72. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth's Andrea Gaston, one of the region's top amateurs, already has 
qualified. She earned an exemption by advancing to the match-play semifinal 
round of the Mid-Amateur last year. STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
