<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Matt McCrite of Westlake Village defeated Ryan O'Neil of Camarillo, 3 and 1, 
to win the match-play final of the Thousand Oaks city junior championship at 
Los Robles Golf Course. 
</P>
<P>
 McCrite, a Westlake High student, shot 68 in the stroke-play portion of the 
event. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Neil, who attends Rio Mesa, shot 71. Softball 
</P>
<P>
 Dodgers Mike Piazza and Eric Karros and other celebrities will challenge Hart, 
a national-champion 10-and-under girls' team from Santa Clarita, in an 
exhibition softball game today at 9 a.m. at Culver City Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-298-7350. Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 West Hills Pony baseball winter season sign-ups are scheduled Saturday from 10 
a.m.-2 p.m. and Wednesday from 5-8 p.m. The season runs from Sept. 17 to Nov. 
20. Players 5 to 17 are eligible. 
</P>
