<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; ON THE ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A mural created by Girls Incorporated of Orange County to celebrate the youth 
organization's 40th anniversary has taken to the road. 
</P>
<P>
 The 8-by-16-foot mural, which traveled to the Orange County Fair, is on 
display through August in the food court at Triangle Square in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 "In the mural, the vast stream of all that is woman -- all of her aspects, 
realities, mysteries, hopes and dreams -- ride forward from a backdrop of a 
brilliant sky at sunset," said artist Paul Redaelli, who collaborated with 
Girls Incorporated to create the work. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizations or businesses that would like to host the mural for display can 
call Girls Incorporated at (714) 646-7181. Exchanging Views 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Weinberg, 17, who will be a senior at Los Alamitos High School, was 
selected to participate in this summer's Youth for Understanding international 
exchange program. He was sponsored by Mitsubishi Motors Corp. of Tokyo, which 
sponsors children of employees of the company's American subsidiaries. 
</P>
<P>
 Weinberg will live with a Japanese family, attend a Japanese high school and 
learn about Japanese culture and customs. 
</P>
