<P>
 Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Leroy Burrell, who set a world 100-meter record of 9.85 seconds last month, 
will miss the rest of the track season because of a foot injury, according to 
Wilfried Meert, director of the Van Damme Memorial meet. Burrell was scheduled 
to run in the meet today at Brussels. 
</P>
